100 Years Ago Today, This is What Was Happening ...

On December 12, 1925, the League of Nations convened in Geneva, discussing disarmament efforts amidst rising tensions in Europe. In Italy, Mussolini continued to consolidate power, emphasizing his regime's fascist ideals. Meanwhile, in the United States, the economy showed signs of growth, with stock prices rising, reflecting optimism in the post-war recovery.
